TY  - JOUR
T1  - Multiattribute Nonlinear Utility Theory
AU  - Fishburn, Peter C.
Y1  - 1984/11/01
PY  - 1984
DA  - 1984/11/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.30.11.1301
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.30.11.1301
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1301
EP  - 1310
VL  - 30
IS  - 11
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Independence axioms similar to those proposed for multiattribute von Neumann?Morgenstern linear utility theory are examined in the context of new nonlinear utility theories developed by Chew and MacCrimmon, and Fishburn. These new theories weaken the independence axiom of von Neumann and Morgenstern, and Fishburn's theory does not require preferences to be transitive. The paper shows that axioms for independence between attributes lead to decompositions of utility for the nonlinear theories that are related to standard decompositions for linear utility.
